      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/5",
      "text": [
        " : \"إِذَا أَرْسَلَ اَلرَّجُلُ كَلْبَهُ وَ نَسِيَ أَنْ يُسَمِّيَ فَهُوَ بِمَنْزِلَةِ مَنْ قَدْ ذَبَحَ وَ نَسِيَ أَنْ يُسَمِّيَ وَ كَذَلِكَ إِذَا رَمَى وَ نَسِيَ أَنْ يُسَمِّيَ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4125 - Musa bin Bakr narrated from Zurara, who reported from Abu Abdullah (as):\n\"If a man sends his hunting dog and forgets to mention the name of Allah (swt), it is like one who slaughters an animal and forgets to mention the name of Allah (swt).\nThe same applies if he shoots (an arrow) and forgets to mention the name of Allah (swt).\""
        ]
      }
    },
